## Lead Roles and Formation

When `/work` is invoked without a specific plan, each instance **self-orients** using the situation report (sitrep) and **self-selects** a lead role. Lead roles have cardinality constraints:

| Role              | Cardinality | Description                                                    | Self-selects when                                                          |
| ----------------- | ----------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| execution-lead    | 1–N         | Grinds through plan tasks via implementer dispatch             | Runnable tasks exist; no other execution-lead on same plan (or slot open). |
| overseer          | 0–1         | Monitors active agents, detects stalls, manages sitrep refresh | 2+ execution-leads active; no overseer claimed.                            |
| investigator-lead | 0–1         | Handles gate:full failures, debug clusters                     | gate:full failed; no investigator-lead active.                             |
| planner-lead      | 0–1         | Runs /plan for queued initiatives/requests                     | Unplanned initiatives exist; no planner-lead active.                       |

**Self-selection algorithm** (for a `/work` instance reading the sitrep):

1. Read the sitrep formation section.
2. Read `tg status --tasks` to see which roles are currently filled (doing tasks, agent names).
3. Pick the highest-priority unfilled role:
   - If gate:full just failed and no investigator-lead → become investigator-lead.
   - If 2+ execution-leads active and no overseer → become overseer.
   - If runnable tasks exist for an unclaimed plan → become execution-lead for that plan.
   - If nothing runnable but unplanned work exists → become planner-lead.
   - If nothing to do → report "all clear" and exit.

The human decides how many `/work` instances to spawn. Each instance reads the sitrep and self-selects. The first instance typically becomes execution-lead (most common need). See docs/leads/README.md (Sitrep and Formation).

